The paper deals with data cleaning and error detection in relational databases, which falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB). The proposed framework, QFix, uses machine learning techniques to analyze query histories and identify potential mistakes, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses optimization techniques to improve the accuracy and performance of the framework, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
